A RESOLUTION
1 Affirming that the American Dream belongs to all of us; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the American Dream has been a beacon of hope for generations; and
3 WHEREAS, the American Dream embodies the ideals of opportunity, prosperity, and
4 upward mobility, promising that every person shall have the chance to achieve what they
5 themselves define as success and fulfillment through hard work and determination; and
6 WHEREAS, many today feel as though their American Dream is unattainable; and
7 WHEREAS, the American Dream belongs to all of us, not just billionaires and
8 multi-millionaires; and
9 WHEREAS, our highest accomplishments as a state and nation have been achieved when we
10 harness the strengths of all people regardless of their identities to overcome our greatest
11 challenges; and
12 WHEREAS, Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion (DEI) is a centuries-old movement deeply
13 rooted in America's founding principles and its subsequent legacy of civil rights and social
