14 justice efforts aimed at delivering the laws, policies, and initiatives that enable America to
15 live up to our Constitution's promises; and
16 WHEREAS, Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion policies, from the 19th Amendment to the 1964
17 Civil Rights Act and the Americans with Disabilities Act, among others, reflect the
18 corrective legislative and legal actions taken across our nation's history to expand and
19 guarantee access to the educational, economic, and civic obligations and capacities of our
20 nation; and
21 WHEREAS, Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion principles and policies promote equal access
22 to opportunities, foster an environment of respect and belonging, and ensure that every
23 individual—regardless of background—can fully participate in all aspects of society; and
24 WHEREAS, Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion is essential to creating a society where all
25 individuals are valued, heard, and included; and
26 WHEREAS, Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion is based on removing barriers to opportunity
27 so that our merits can speak for themselves; and
28 WHEREAS, Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion is committed to widening pathways to the
29 American Dream for every community so that all people can reap the benefits of shared
30 prosperity in our nation; and
31 WHEREAS, freedom of speech and expression are fundamental constitutional rights,
32 protecting the ability of individuals to voice their ideas and opinions without interference,
33 punishment, or retaliation by the government; and
